title: Allow Root Login via SSH in Linux
tags: @zettel _method ssh linux
roam-id: 490baa6d-f022-4266-b699-c070a2b6aee6
type: text/markdown

- login to your server as a normal user
- edit `/etc/ssh/sshd_config` file
- uncomment `PermitRootLogin prohibit-password`
- replace the line with `PermitRootLogin yes`
- save an exit the file
- restart ssh service by `sudo systemctl restart ssh.service`
- now you can login as `root` from another machine
